The House of Representatives Committee on Emergency and Disaster Preparedness on Thursday resolved to invite Vice President Yemi Osinbajo to appear and testify before it over the suspension of some senior staff of the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA). The vice president, who is the chairman of the NEMA board, is to explain why the board "arbitrarily suspended" six senior staff without following due process. Members of the panel said during an investigative hearing in Abuja that it was curious that the NEMA board suspended the staff the same day it was inaugurated. The panel, presided by the deputy chairman, Ali Isa (PDP, Gombe), wondered why such an action would be taken without recourse to the rule of law. NEMA Director General, Mustapha Maihaja, had told the panel that the six staff were suspended as a result of the demand by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), which is investigating corruption allegations involving some staff of the agency.  Details later...